WHO: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Everyone (No advance registration required - space is limited)
DATE: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Wednesday nights
TIME: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 7:00&ndash;8:30&nbsp;PM
WHERE: &nbsp; &nbsp; Building 300,&nbsp;Wayside Chapel, San Antonio, Texas



&nbsp;

After centuries of God ruling His people through judges, Israel demanded a king like other nations, thereby rejecting the Lord. So the Lord directed the prophet Samuel to appoint a king, Saul,&nbsp;who ruled&nbsp;according to his flesh even as the Lord prepared another man, David, after His own heart.

Learn how Israel moved to become&nbsp;a nation under a king and how the Lord used Israel&#39;s impatience&nbsp;to demonstrate the inadequacy of human rulers in solving the problem of the nation&#39;s sin and apostasy. In addition to telling this story of Saul and David, the book of&nbsp;1Samuel introduces other&nbsp;well-known biblical characters in scripture including&nbsp;Jonathan, Mephibosheth&nbsp;and others.&nbsp;

Pastor Armstrong teaches this year-long study through 1 Samuel&nbsp;in his notable in-depth, insightful style. Join us for this popular Old Testament book study.

The class meets weekly on Wednesday evenings from 7:00-8:30 PM, in Building 300 of Wayside Chapel.&nbsp;Students of all ages are welcome. Childcare is not available.&nbsp;

For more information, please contact the ministry. Seating in limited. Previously recorded&nbsp;lessons can be found on the 1Samuel Bible Study page.

