WHO: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Single&nbsp;and Married Adults &nbsp;(Advanced invitation required)
DATE:&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;June 11-14, 2016 &nbsp;
TIME: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Various times
WHERE: &nbsp; Le Grandeur Johor Bahru, Malaysia

&nbsp;

Join Pastor Stephen Armstrong in Malaysia for a special, three-day intensive study on the biblical principles of marriage and family taught at the Le Grandeur Johor Bahru resort in Malaysia. Pastor Armstrong joins Pastor Yuk Yee Foo and the congregation of Living Praise Presbyterian Church in Singapore to reflect on Christian marriage in an age of changing morality and values. &nbsp;&nbsp;



The church camp offers three days of in-depth teaching by Pastor&nbsp;Armstrong and Pastor Yuk Yee and their wives on various topics including&nbsp;Biblical view of marriage and singleness in service to God,&nbsp;roles of husbands and wives, the roles for men and women in the church, biblical parenting, &amp; family discipleship, and worldly relationships, including common unchristian views of marriage roles, sexual relationships, &amp; family environment.

In addition to the teaching, the camp offers workshops for men and women as well as&nbsp;group assignments where attendees can discuss and apply the principles under review.

The camp takes place at the Le Grandeur Johor Bahru in&nbsp;Malaysia&nbsp;primarily for the members of Living Praise Presbyterian Church of Singapore with limited space available&nbsp;for non-church members.

Please contact the church office directly to request an invitation to attend. You may contact the church by email or by phone at +65 6259 1943. A fee will be assessed for nonchurch members to cover lodging and food.

&nbsp;



